{"body": "We're just talking about a default here, right?\r\n\r\nCompiled assets are ephemeral. If you lose them, it is trivial to recreate them.\r\n\r\nGit repositories are opaque to a lot of developers. If you bloat them, it is trivial to prune them.\r\n\r\nIf the default isn't what you want, it's recoverable either way. But there's more work to pruning a git repository than there is to recompiling assets.\r\n\r\nSo it seems to me that the lesser evil is to ignore precompiled assets by default.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3266758", "created_at": "2011-12-24T06:26:47Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2817#issuecomment-3266758", "updated_at": "2011-12-24T06:26:47Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 2817, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheldonh/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheldonh/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheldonh/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheldonh", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheldonh/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/sheldonh", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheldonh/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/747b0480986bd8ac5d91aafd74bea043?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fcf7f5d18c19536b2299bd648d5028f0c.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheldonh/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheldonh/received_events", "gravatar_id": "747b0480986bd8ac5d91aafd74bea043", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheldonh/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "sheldonh", "type": "User", "id": 45098, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sheldonh/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52383ed6bd3543c15101061a"}, "id": 3266758, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2817"}
